(79, 'putera-sampoerna-foundation-annual-report-2021-2', NULL, 'Putera Sampoerna Foundation Annual Report 2021', NULL, '<!-- wp:file {\"id\":6923,\"href\":\"https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Yayasan-Putera-Sampoerna_Billingual_Report_2021.pdf\",\"showDownloadButton\":false,\"displayPreview\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><object class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Yayasan-Putera-Sampoerna_Billingual_Report_2021.pdf\" type=\"application/pdf\" style=\"width:100%;height:600px\" aria-label=\"Yayasan Putera Sampoerna_Billingual_Report_2021\"></object><a id=\"wp-block-file--media-8c0237bb-a1ad-4086-b087-44d906d9246b\" href=\"https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Yayasan-Putera-Sampoerna_Billingual_Report_2021.pdf\">Yayasan Putera Sampoerna_Billingual_Report_2021</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:file -->', 'https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/unsplash_nApaSgkzaxg-e1691553906259-1.png', 'en', 1, 'https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/putera-sampoerna-foundation-annual-report-2021-2/', '[\"Annual Report\"]', '2022-05-25 19:57:06', '2024-12-22 07:56:31'),
(80, 'high-quality-education-system', NULL, 'High Quality Education System: A Review of Sampoerna Academy', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E86\">Every parent wishes to provide&nbsp;the best&nbsp;education system and&nbsp;educational facilities for&nbsp;their&nbsp;children.&nbsp;They&nbsp;hope that their&nbsp;children&nbsp;can grow and develop into better&nbsp;people. Thatâs why&nbsp;some parents choose to send their children to&nbsp;an&nbsp;international elementary school instead of&nbsp;a&nbsp;regular elementary school.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E112\">Today,&nbsp;parents&nbsp;have a lot of alternatives to choose from; they can choose one that meets their needs and suits&nbsp;their little ones.&nbsp;Sampoerna Academy international elementary school is one of them.&nbsp;With Sampoerna Academy, you can provide high-quality&nbsp;education&nbsp;for your children.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"E124\"><strong>The Learning Methods at Sampoerna Academy International Elementary School</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":6842,\"width\":841,\"height\":555,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/schoolchildren-reading-library_1098-4048.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-6842\" style=\"width:841px;height:555px\" width=\"841\" height=\"555\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E127\">As an international school, Sampoerna Academy has different learningÂ approaches andÂ methods compared toÂ those ofÂ regular schools. There are sevenÂ keyÂ factorsÂ ofÂ theÂ educationÂ systemÂ offeredÂ at Sampoerna Academy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"E145\"><strong>1. A Collaborative Education System</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E147\">Sampoerna Academy&nbsp;sets up&nbsp;a collaborative education system.&nbsp;Students get&nbsp;more than just&nbsp;a&nbsp;one-way learning direction where teachers&nbsp;explain the whole subject in front of the class.&nbsp;At Sampoerna Academy,&nbsp;students can be actively involved in their&nbsp;learning process. They can also develop their&nbsp;ability to solve problems and share knowledge.&nbsp;This way,&nbsp;Sampoerna Academy&nbsp;contributes&nbsp;to&nbsp;making&nbsp;Indonesia a country with the best education system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"E174\"><strong>2. Child Development Portfolio</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E176\">The education system at&nbsp;Sampoerna Academyâs international elementary school is&nbsp;equipped with an extensive range of&nbsp;supporting data, including studentsâ&nbsp;development portfolios.&nbsp;The&nbsp;portfolios are&nbsp;stored in&nbsp;the schoolâs&nbsp;Google Drive and continuously updated as&nbsp;the&nbsp;students&nbsp;progress from time to time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E198\">The&nbsp;portfolios&nbsp;feature&nbsp;comprehensive&nbsp;documentation of studentsâ&nbsp;academic and social development&nbsp;that&nbsp;will&nbsp;be used by the school&nbsp;to&nbsp;evaluate their&nbsp;learning process.&nbsp;These&nbsp;portfolios&nbsp;also work&nbsp;as a&nbsp;medium to show parents&nbsp;how&nbsp;their&nbsp;children&nbsp;have developed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"E236\"><strong>3. Basic Programming Skills</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E238\">At&nbsp;Sampoerna Academy,&nbsp;elementary&nbsp;school students&nbsp;learn&nbsp;basic programming skills.&nbsp;Learning programming&nbsp;skills&nbsp;can&nbsp;help&nbsp;students develop their&nbsp;abilities&nbsp;to use logic and think critically.&nbsp;Whatâs more, instead of practicing the skills in a regular programming class, students at Sampoerna Academy learn&nbsp;in a fun LEGO robotics class.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"E262\"><strong>4.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://steamindonesia.id/\">STEAM</a>-based Learning</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E265\">Sampoerna Academy students&nbsp;learn in a true education system&nbsp;that leverages&nbsp;the STEAM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts, and Math)&nbsp;perspectives. In&nbsp;the STEAM-based&nbsp;learning&nbsp;approach, students&nbsp;are&nbsp;encouraged to carry out various practical activities to stimulate their curiosity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E280\">However,&nbsp;it doesnât stop there. Students&nbsp;also get&nbsp;a wide range of&nbsp;opportunities to express&nbsp;their&nbsp;hypotheses, findings, and methodologies to their peers.&nbsp;Moreover, through various presentations they&nbsp;must&nbsp;prepare and conduct,&nbsp;students&nbsp;can develop their&nbsp;self-confidence and&nbsp;critical thinking skills&nbsp;at the same time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"E304\"><strong>5. International standards</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E306\">The&nbsp;title&nbsp;âinternational elementary schoolâ&nbsp;at Sampoerna Academyâs name&nbsp;isnât just&nbsp;a title.&nbsp;Sampoerna Academy&nbsp;always&nbsp;ensures that the implementation of teaching and learning activities&nbsp;at the school&nbsp;meets&nbsp;international standards.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E329\">Thatâs why&nbsp;Sampoerna Academy&nbsp;regularly&nbsp;benchmarks its performance&nbsp;by taking&nbsp;the Measures of Academic Progress (MAP) test&nbsp;published by&nbsp;the North Evaluation Association (NWEA).&nbsp;The MAP test assesses&nbsp;individual performance in terms of reading, science, and math skills.&nbsp;There&nbsp;are other tests from Cambridge and the Indonesian Ministry of Education that are&nbsp;also&nbsp;useful for measuring the effectiveness of Sampoerna Academyâs&nbsp;education&nbsp;programs. The test results then become a&nbsp;medium&nbsp;of evaluation&nbsp;to&nbsp;encourage&nbsp;studentsâ academic development efforts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"E357\"><strong>6. Specialist Teachers for Grade 4 and Up</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E360\">Sampoerna Academy provides specialist teachers&nbsp;to teach students who&nbsp;enter&nbsp;Grade 4.&nbsp;Specialist teachers&nbsp;teach various subjects, including&nbsp;Reading,&nbsp;Mathematics,&nbsp;Computer&nbsp;Science,&nbsp;Science, and&nbsp;Foreign&nbsp;Languages.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"E385\"><strong>7. High-Tech Classrooms</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E387\">Finally, Sampoerna Academy&nbsp;always&nbsp;ensures&nbsp;that students&nbsp;can&nbsp;learn&nbsp;in&nbsp;a&nbsp;comfortable and calm&nbsp;environment.&nbsp;Thatâs why Sampoerna Academy buildings consist of&nbsp;classrooms&nbsp;that are equipped with advanced technology&nbsp;to support&nbsp;studentsâ&nbsp;learning&nbsp;activities.&nbsp;Students can also utilize&nbsp;iPads&nbsp;and Chromebook devices&nbsp;completed&nbsp;with various supporting&nbsp;software provided by the school.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"E421\">With&nbsp;a perfect&nbsp;education system as advanced as above,&nbsp;itâs&nbsp;no wonder that Sampoerna Academy&nbsp;international&nbsp;elementary&nbsp;school&nbsp;becomes&nbsp;the right&nbsp;school&nbsp;for&nbsp;your children.&nbsp;By providing excellent education,&nbsp;Sampoerna Academy is also actively contributing to helping Indonesia become&nbsp;one of the countries with the best education system in Southeast Asia. Through the support of&nbsp;high-quality learning&nbsp;approaches and methods,&nbsp;students at Sampoerna Academy&nbsp;will be able to grow&nbsp;into young people who are highly competitive at the global level. For further information regarding registration and school visits at Sampoerna Academy,&nbsp;donât hesitate to get in touch with&nbsp;us&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.sampoernaacademy.sch.id/en/sa-in-numbers/\">here</a>!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/classmates-holding-folders_1098-1068-e1684218572758.png', 'en', 1, 'https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/high-quality-education-system/', '[\"Education Article\",\"News\",\"SSS\"]', '2022-03-30 06:32:00', '2024-12-22 07:56:31'),
(81, 'sa-surabaya-received-a-grade-a-from-the-national-library', NULL, 'SA Surabaya Received a Grade A from the National Library', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Surabaya, December 2, 2021</strong>&nbsp;â The library of Sampoerna Academy Surabaya international school has been awarded a Grade A for its excellent facilities. The grade was awarded based on an assessment to several essential areas: the collection owned, infrastructure and facilities, services, personnel, operations and management, and other supporting components. The accreditation was conducted by the team from the National Library of the Republic of Indonesia and involved a thorough evaluation to each area indicator. As a part of the process, Sampoerna Academy Surabaya officially registered its library in March 2021 and submitted the final supporting documents last September.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>âWe are proud that, after a long appraisal process, our school finally received a Grade A. This, of course, has further solidified Sampoerna Academyâs commitment in providing internationally recognized education to our students, and one of the ways is by having a high-quality library,â stated&nbsp;<strong>John Murphy, the Principal of Sampoerna Academy Surabaya</strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Literacy, he added, is an important element of studentsâ learning process, and libraries are a means to improve literacy among students. Therefore, it is important for a school to ensure various kinds of literature are available for their students.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>âWe implement a concept of education called STEAM, which refers to Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts, and Mathematics. This method has been proven to be successful in shaping students into individuals who have competence in the areas of communication, collaboration, creativity, critical thinking, and character â or what we call the 5Cs. [When it comes to] supporting the achievement of this goal, libraries play an important role in accelerating the process.â</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By providing more than 5000 items in its collection, the Sampoerna Academy Surabaya library is aiming to become an effective library in developing studentsâ literacy skills. The library also constantly publishes an extensive list of creative and innovative works. Whatâs more, it regularly holds various literacy programs which are open not only to students, but also to the public, while still implementing the STEAM approach to pique the interest and promote the literacy culture among the younger generations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>âWith a collection of mostly non-fiction books, e-books, audio-visual books, and subscription-based newspapers and tabloids, we believe that our goal to create a literate society through our library will be easier to achieve. We educate the children within the school environment to love reading, love libraries, and love doing research.â</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Besides offering a wide range of literature collection, the Sampoerna Academy Surabaya library also continuously makes various innovations to help the school accomplish its vision and mission. There are several innovations that received positive remarks from the National Library of Indonesia: the provision of robotic toys to support the curriculum, a Library Drive-Thru system where students can borrow books from home and pick the items up at school, the use of iPad for reading, and the Sampoerna Corner where the works of Sampoerna Academy students, teachers, and their families are displayed together.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>âWhatâs more, we also feature our uniqueness to be experienced by visitors, especially children; for example, [we have]&nbsp;<em>a story time place</em>&nbsp;or a place for storytelling, an attractive room, shelves that were specially designed to make it easier for students to pick up books, and comfortable seats for reading activities.â</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With this honor bestowed, Sampoerna Academy Surabaya is evermore committed to continue its mission to provide various sources of information for students, reinforcing their ever-growing knowledge and love of reading.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>âThis library will be the center of information literacy, idea literacy, and concept literacy for our students in the future,â he concluded.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/361483871-press-release-sa-surabaya-library-02-1.jpg', 'en', 1, 'https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/sa-surabaya-received-a-grade-a-from-the-national-library/', '[\"Education Article\",\"News\",\"SSS\"]', '2022-01-20 08:04:00', '2024-12-22 07:56:31'),
(82, 'sa-is-ready-to-open-its-second-school-in-surabaya-in-2022', NULL, 'SA Is Ready to Open Its Second School in Surabaya in 2022', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Surabaya, December 2, 2021</strong>&nbsp;â Reaffirming its commitment in creating a future generation with 21st century competencies,&nbsp;<strong>the pioneer of STEAM education, Sampoerna Academy,</strong>&nbsp;is launching its second school in Surabaya. Located in one of the most strategic areas in Surabaya, Sampoerna Academy Grand Pakuwon will be home to 30 ultra-modern classrooms and various international standard indoor and outdoor facilities specifically designed for 21st century education. Whatâs more, the learning experience at Sampoerna Academy Grand Pakuwon is perfected with the best international programs for all levels of education, from early childhood to higher education. As the newest, largest, and fastest growing international school in Surabaya, Sampoerna Academy Grand Pakuwon is ready to welcome students and parents for the upcoming 2022 academic year.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>John Murphy, the Principal of Sampoerna Academy Surabaya,</strong>&nbsp;stated, âIt is Sampoerna Academyâs commitment to continuously provide high-quality international standard education to create excellent future generations. One of the ways is by launching our seventh campus in Indonesia, or the second in Surabaya, for the upcoming 2022 academic year. We continue to strive to provide a safe, caring, and collaborative learning environment [for our students] and support [their] learning process through the STEAM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts, and Mathematics) approach.â</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to the data released by&nbsp;<strong>the World Bank,</strong>&nbsp;in 2020, the Indonesia&nbsp;<strong>Human Capital Index</strong>&nbsp;score was 0,54% with a low level of global competence (rank 96th out of 173 countries). This means that Indonesia needs to increase the competence level of its human resources from an early age to make sure they can compete globally. The opening of Sampoerna Academy Grand Pakuwon is in line with the governmentâs mission to improve the quality of Indonesiaâs human resources and the level of its global competence. Moreover, as the second Sampoerna Academy school in Surabaya, Sampoerna Academy Grand Pakuwon also aims to meet the high demand for international education in Surabaya.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>âBesides [believing in] international standard education that implements the STEAM approach and focuses on developing 5C skills in students â communication, collaboration, creativity, critical thinking, and character, we also believe in the importance of complete school facilities which can support the academic and non-academic development of our students,â he added.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Based on that belief, Sampoerna Academy Grand Pakuwon was specifically and efficiently designed to be equipped with a number of high-standard educational facilities, including spacious and comfortable classrooms, soccer and basketball fields, a swimming pool, a music and dance room, an outdoor playroom, and a multifunction room to support various student activities. Whatâs more, Sampoerna Academy Grand Pakuwon is also completed with more than one laboratory â each dedicated for different subjects: Biology, Chemistry, and Physics â which have been set up according to the standards and specifications established for the Cambridge International Curriculum. a</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>âWith the opening of Sampoerna Academy Grand Pakuwon for the 2022 academic year, we hope to meet the needs of parents and students in Surabaya for an internationally recognized education that focuses on developing [studentsâ] 21st century competencies,â he concluded.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/361483865-press-release-sas-grand-pakuwon-1920-x-500-01-1.jpg', 'en', 1, 'https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/sa-is-ready-to-open-its-second-school-in-surabaya-in-2022/', '[\"Education Article\",\"News\",\"SSS\"]', '2022-01-19 08:17:00', '2024-12-22 07:56:31'),
(83, 'sa-held-healing-earth-through-arts-hearts-workshop', NULL, 'SA Held Healing Earth Through Arts (HEARTs) Workshop', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Jakarta, October 30, 2021</strong>&nbsp;â The intercultural school and pioneer of STEAM in Indonesia, Sampoerna Academy, reaffirmed its commitment to always provide the best education in Indonesia in order to shape a future generation that is able to compete globally and has high empathy for social and sustainability causes. As part of the&nbsp;<em>United Nations Day</em>&nbsp;commemoration which falls in October, Sampoerna Academy collaborated with the&nbsp;<strong>Rumah Main StrEAM</strong>&nbsp;community to hold a fun, interactive, and educational program titled&nbsp;<strong>Healing Earth Through Arts (HEARTs)</strong>&nbsp;where children turned waste and scrap into arts and crafts through the Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts, and Mathematics (STEAM) approach.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Maharsi Palupining Rini, S. S., the National Principal of Sampoerna Academy Surabaya</strong>, stated that Sampoerna Academyâs mission has always been to provide the best education in Indonesia which is in line with one of the&nbsp;<em>Tujuan Pembangunan Berkelanjutan (TPB)</em>&nbsp;or Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs): to ensure inclusive and equitable high-quality education and promote lifelong learning opportunities for all.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>âAs an educational institution, it is very important for us to continue to support the TPB program by encouraging the creation of future generations who are critical, able to compete, and aspire to make a better world. The UN Week program was more than just a celebration; it was an emphasis on studentsâ and the younger generationsâ social awareness and empathy on the issues of sustainability and climate change from an early age,â she said in Jakarta (30/10).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Yuni Widiastuti, the Founder and Initiator of Komunitas Ibu Rumah Main STrEAM</strong>, also expressed the same thing. âThrough the opportunity to play that we have just experienced, we have become more aware and optimistic that the role of parents and the community is very valuable in developing their childrenâs 21st century skills. Disruptions are occurring, one of which is a disruption in climate change and our environment. Will there be a second Earth for us? This question, of course, can only be answered by our children when they grow up,â she said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Therefore, Yuni added, through the activity of learning while playing which involved the experiments to utilize waste and scrap around, Rumah Main STrEAM and Sampoerna Academy wanted to invite parents and the community to actively participate in implementing the STEAM-based education. âBy providing 15-30 minutes for children to play meaningfully from an early age, [we hope to] see that the Earth [continues to be] alright, because children who have been educated from an early age [will] understand that our Mother Earth needs to be protected and not just exploited.â</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Through this program, as a pioneer of STEAM in Indonesia, Sampoerna Academy hoped to support the development of the Indonesian childrenâs 5C skills (<strong>Critical Thinking, Communication, Collaboration, Creativity,&nbsp;</strong>and<strong>&nbsp;Character</strong>) using the STEAM approach, while recognizing the&nbsp;<strong>IGNITE</strong>&nbsp;values&nbsp;<strong>ââ(Integrity, Growth Mindset, Nobility, Innovation, Teamwork,&nbsp;</strong>and<strong>&nbsp;Excellence)</strong>. Sampoerna Academy has been consistently instilling these values ââinto all students because we see IGNITE as one of the keys to ensure that the future generations of Indonesia have a high level of social empathy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>âSampoerna Academy hopes that this program can be a meaningful step in the journey of Indonesian children to create a better earth and world. Even though it looks like a simple program, we believe it will grant us results and [encourage] positive changes in them to see the importance of sustainability for their future,â Palupi concluded.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/361483885-press-release-sa-hearts-workshop-1920-x-500-01-1.jpg', 'en', 1, 'https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/sa-held-healing-earth-through-arts-hearts-workshop/', '[\"Education Article\",\"News\",\"SSS\"]', '2022-01-18 08:19:00', '2024-12-22 07:56:31'),
(84, 'sampoerna-academy-students-teachers-launch-self-written-e-book', NULL, 'Sampoerna Academy Students &#038; Teachers Launch Self-written E-book', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To celebrate International Literacy Day that falls on the 8th of September, Sampoerna Academy launched an e-book that speaks of the importance of responsibility &amp; family.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This book â a collaborative effort between students &amp; teachers â was launched as an effort to help improve the literacy level and reading interest of Indonesiaâs younger generation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Literacy is a Foundation</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Literacy is an essential foundation for the advancement provision of the future generation of Indonesia. However, Indonesia is still facing a low level of literacy and reading interest at the moment. Based on&nbsp;<strong>Reading Literacy Activity Index (Alibaca) research</strong>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<strong>2019</strong>&nbsp;by&nbsp;<strong>the Ministry of Education</strong>, the average of National Alibaca Index in 34 provinces is at&nbsp;<strong>37.32%&nbsp;</strong>(relatively low), along with the two lowest dimensional index values, which are the dimension of&nbsp;<strong>Access</strong>&nbsp;and the dimension of&nbsp;<strong>Culture</strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, the research also found one of the determining indicators in the&nbsp;<strong>Alternative</strong>&nbsp;dimensions can be an opportunity to overcome this issue by utilizing the digital platform alternatives. With&nbsp;<strong>95.25%&nbsp;</strong>average number of Home Internet Access and Activity of Indonesians above 5years old (including browsing, chatting, and social media performance), Indonesia still has the opportunity to improve Its literacy levels by providing accessible and appealing educational books options through an online platform</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Adelina Holmes â Head of Literacy &amp; English Department from Sampoerna Academy says: âSampoerna Academy is committed to create a quality future generation through the best education. We believe that literacy is a fundamental element to achieve that, therefore it is crucial to habitualize reading from a young age. This is also why weâre doing the Literacy Festival with the main agenda being the launch of&nbsp;<em>Elidi &amp; The Ancestorâs Garden</em>&nbsp;which is dedicated to all Indonesian children. We hope that this book can answer the needs of interesting &amp; quality reading materials that can booster cognitive &amp; linguistic abilities for children ages 6-12 years old.â</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Indonesiaâs Reading Ambassador &amp; Rumah Dunia Founder, Gol A Gong expresses the following: âI am very amazed to see the work that the Sampoerna Academy students has produced. In my opinion, the support that a school provides for their student so that they continually create, in this context launching a book, is exemplary and should be given the highest appreciation. As a reading ambassador, I see this Literacy Festival as a program that is interesting and very much needed, especially for generation Z &amp; Alpha. This initiative by Sampoerna Academy is key in helping to make the program of growing the interest of reading and writing in Indonesia, a success.â</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>So letâs start reading!</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Get to know Elidi &amp; his friends through the adventure of&nbsp;<em>Elidi &amp; The Ancestorâs Garden</em>.</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":4097,\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://www.sampoernaacademy.sch.id/en/literacy-festival-2021/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img src=\"https://www.sampoernaacademy.sch.id/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/SA-Lit-Fest-2021-Web-Page-Asset_download-button-300x59.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4097\"/></a></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/SA-LitFest-News-Banner-01a-1.jpg', 'en', 1, 'https://www.sampoernafoundation.org/sampoerna-academy-students-teachers-launch-self-written-e-book/', '[\"Education Article\",\"News\",\"SSS\"]', '2021-09-16 08:24:00', '2024-12-22 07:56:31'),
